A woman has been arrested after a man was killed when a car hit two pedestrians.Ambulance crews called to the junction of Boldmere Road and Redacre Road in Sutton Coldfield found a male pedestrian receiving life support from the fire service."Sadly, it quickly became clear he could not be saved and was confirmed dead at the scene," a West Midlands Ambulance Service spokesperson said.Police said the driver was arrested at the scene on suspicion of causing death by dangerous driving and remains in custody.
The second pedestrian, also a man, was treated by ambulance staff for minor injuries.West Midlands Police is appealing to any witnesses or anyone who may have dashcam, CCTV or doorbell footage to come forward.
